Package oracle.ateam.sample.mobile.v2.persistence.metadata

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MethodHeaderParameter
    Interface that defines SOAP method header parameter or RESTful resource header parameter
    MethodParameter
    Interface that defines SOAP method parameter or RESTful resource parameter
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AttributeMapping
    Superclass of all attribute mapping classes.
    AttributeMappingDirect
    Mapping class that returns information for entity attributes that are directly mapped to a table column The information is read from the persistenceMapping xml file as configured in mobile-persistence-config.properties
    AttributeMappingOneToMany
    Mapping class that returns information for entity attributes that are mapped to a child collection.
    AttributeMappingOneToOne
    Mapping class that returns information for entity attributes that are mapped one-to-one to another entity.
    ClassMappingDescriptor
    Class that returns entity-level information about the mapping of this entity to a database table.
    Method
    Class that represents a method instance as defined in persistenceMapping.xml file.
    MethodHeaderParameterImpl
    Implementation of SOAP method header parameter or REST resource header parameter that can be instantiated programmatically
    MethodParameterImpl
    Implementation of SOAP method parameter or REST resource parameter that can be instantiated programmatically
    OAuthConfig  
    ObjectPersistenceMapping
    Class that maps to the top-level node in the persistenceMapping XML file
    PersistenceConfig
    Helper class that returns the information defined in the mobile-persistence-config.properties file, that should be located in the META-INF directory of your ApplicationCPOntroller project.
    XMLMethodHeaderParameter
    Implementation of SOAP method header parameter or REST resource header parameter that reads values from persistenceMapping.xml
    XMLMethodParameter
    Implementation of SOAP method parameter or REST resource parameter that reads values from persistenceMapping.xml
